<item>
            <title>[OAK-3567] Long running query holds TreeLock</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-3567</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Merges to the 1.0 and 1.2 branches caused by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2829&quot; title=&quot;Comparing node states for external changes is too slow&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-2829&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-2829&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; accidentally reverted some of the &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-3023&quot; title=&quot;Long running MongoDB query may block other threads&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-3023&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-3023&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fix. This causes long running queries to still acquire the TreeLock and block other operations.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
